Description: Jacob's jouney into Egypt; to right, Jacob seated on a horse leading a procession of animals including donkeys, sheep, camels, cows and dogs, accompanied by several walking figures, a woman and baby riding on a horse, and a further procession of people and animals descending a hill to left behind. c. c.1647 Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Stefano della Bella
Curator's comments: BM also has an impression of the third state: see X,5.1.
